<title>EGYPT: Egypt offers two government firms for lease.</title>
<headline>Egypt offers two government firms for lease.</headline>
<dateline>CAIRO 1997-04-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Egypt's state-owned Textiles Industries Holding Company said on Monday it was inviting foreign and local investors to manage or lease two of its subsidiaries as part of the state's privatisation programme.</p>
<p>It said in a published announcement that qualified investors could bid for either Arab Carpet and Upholstery or Cairo Deying and Finishing.</p>
<p>Investors can buy detailed documents at the holding company. Deadline for the bid is noon (1000 GMT) on May 5.</p>
<p>The government has in the past tried to sell-off the firms to strategic investors but officials said the bids were not attractive enough.</p>
<p>$1 = 3.395</p>
